President Biden visited Abbott's Creek Community Center in Raleigh, North Carolina to discuss the progress being made in investing in America and expanding access to affordable high-speed internet. He highlighted the importance of high-speed internet as a necessity in today's world, especially for education, work, and healthcare. The President announced an additional investment of $82 million to connect 16,000 homes and businesses in North Carolina to high-speed internet. He also emphasized the creation of jobs in the manufacturing sector, particularly in the production of fiber-optic cable, and the positive impact of these investments on the economy. President Biden reiterated his commitment to being a president for all Americans and working together to achieve progress and growth.